The paper discusses deep learning models and their privacy implications, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses attacks on privacy-preserving collaborative deep learning, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) in the attack suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also discusses differential privacy (DP), which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS).
